:Paul Leyland speaks of indicators of one's "personal" literary style. One
:wonders if there is a program to analyze text and prepare some sort of
:numerical profile which can easily be compared to yet other sample of text
:in order to try to match authorship.

Yes, but it needs a large corpus of both authors' styles.  Professor Sidney
Michaelson of Edinburgh University pioneered this work with the Rev Andrew
Morton.  They were often called as expert witnesses in trials during the
seventies.  (Usually for the prosecution)

G
